    <h2>Interesting facts about cats</h2>
    
    <!-- Ordered List -->
    <ol>
        <li>Purring: Cats purr to express emotions and even heal themselves.</li>
        <li>Night Vision: They can see in very low light, almost six times better than humans.</li>
        <li>Whiskers: Their whiskers help them navigate and sense changes in their environment.</li>
        <li>Falling Reflex: Cats have a "righting reflex" that helps them land on their feet from heights.</li>
        <li>Stealthy Hunters: Padded paws make them silent and skilled hunters.</li>
    </ol>

    

